      • SelfJoin_planeSweep

        public static <S extends Shape> int SelfJoin_planeSweep(S[] R,
                                        boolean refine,
                                        org.apache.hadoop.mapred.OutputCollector<S,S> output,
                                        Progressable reporter)
                               throws IOException
        The general version of self join algorithm which works with arbitrary shapes. First, it performs a filter step where it finds shapes with overlapping MBRs. Second, an optional refine step can be executed to return only shapes which actually overlap.
        Parameters:
        R - - input set of shapes
        refine - - Whether or not to run a refine step
        output - - output collector where the results are reported
        Returns:
        - number of pairs returned by the planesweep algorithm
        Throws:
        IOException

      • unionGroup

        public static int unionGroup(com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.Geometry[] geoms,
             Progressable prog,
             ResultCollector<com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.Geometry> output)
                      throws IOException
        Union a group of (overlapping) geometries. It runs as follows.
        1. All polygons are sorted by the x-dimension of their left most point
        2. We run a plane-sweep algorithm that keeps merging polygons in batches of 500 objects
        3. As soon as part of the answer is to the left of the sweep-line, it is finalized and reported to the output
        4. As the sweep line reaches the far right, all remaining polygons are merged and the answer is reported
        Parameters:
        geoms -
        Returns:
        Throws:
        IOException

      • multiUnion

        public static int multiUnion(com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.Geometry[] geoms,
             Progressable prog,
             ResultCollector<com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.Geometry> output)
                      throws IOException
        Computes the union of multiple groups of polygons. The algorithm runs in the following steps.
        1. The polygons are flattened using flattenGeometries(Geometry[]) to extract the simplest form of them
        2. Polygons are grouped into groups of overlapping polygons using groupPolygons(Geometry[], Progressable) so that we can compute the answer of each group separately
        3. The union of each group is computed using the unionGroup(Geometry[], Progressable, ResultCollector) function
        Parameters:
        geoms -
        prog -
        output -
        Returns:
        Throws:
        IOException
